					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12496767#post-4509649</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12496767/scp-4773-2#post-4509649</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 21 Feb 2020 02:14:24 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>NatVoltaic</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2800867</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>While I really want to like this article &#8212; the execution is clever as hell and it's paced the right way to carry a punch &#8212; having a story simply be &quot;a child dies tragically,&quot; with no extra meaning to it, comes across as hollow. It reads like cruelty for cruelty's sake without having a tangible message. The implied bureaucracy failures could add more to that, but it's given so little focus that it reads less like a direct, tangible failure and more an unfortunate incident outside of the Foundation's control or anyone's control. And, while this is likely a consequence of my interests in the wiki shifting, that holds nothing for me.</p> <p>Reluctant -1.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
