					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12496767#post-4387458</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12496767/scp-4773-2#post-4387458</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 04 Oct 2019 11:56:31 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Henzoid</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5190300</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Well, actually, that's one of the hardest concepts to grasp/write about in terms of antimemetics. Depending on the piece, and the author, antimemetic SCPs can have different properties.</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">For&nbsp;Example:</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">For&nbsp;Example:</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>SCP-4773-1 can't be comprehended at all, so even if it would seem obvious that he's there in the background, it is impossible for that information to compile in the researchers' minds. Then you have antimemes like 055, which CAN be comprehended, it just removes information about itself in post.</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
